<TITLE> Siraj, Moni head BCB key committees </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 2 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Cricket Board has on Tuesday finalised the top guns of all its 16 standing committees in the second meeting of the BCB board of directors at Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium. Enayet Hossain Siraj has been named chairman of the Cricket Operation while former board general secretary Aminul Haq Moni appointed chairman of the Game Development Committee. Gazi Ashraf Hossain Lipu, former cricket operation chairman of the ad-hoc committee, has been given the responsibility of tournament committee while senior vice president Mahbubul Anam will head the working committee. Jalal Younus has been appointed chairman of the media and communications committee in place of Ahmed Sajjdul Alam Bobby, who earlier served the same post in the ad-hoc committee. Bobby was made chairman of the disciplinary committee. Aziz Al Kaiser regained his previous chairman post of the marketing and commercial committee while ad-hoc committee member-turned-director Shafiqur Rahman Munna also retained the grounds and facilities chairmanship. GS Hasan Chowdhury Tamim has been appointed chairman of the cricket committee of Dhaka Metropolis. Chairmen of other committees are: Ahmed Iqbal Hasan (finance committee), Mahmood Jamal (umpires committee), Syed Zahid Hossain (medical committee), Mirza Salman Ispahani (tender & purchase committee), Feroz Ahmed (audit committee), Abdullah Al Fuad Redwan (women's wing) and M Mizanur Rahman (logistics & protocol committee). The chairmen of the respective committees will co-opt members to complete the full committees at their disposal later. bd
